NAPWG - Not Another PassWord Generator

Description

napwg is a command line tool for generate strong passwords.

napwg consists of a single, stand-alone executable file which does not 
require or keeps any special config or data files, each time napwg is 
called all entropy sources are calculated from scratch. napwg uses 
several sources simultaneously to produce strong unpredictably passwords.

This program is free software: you can redistribute it and/or modify it 
under the terms of the GNU General Public License as published by the 
Free Software Foundation, either version 3 of the License, or (at your 
option) any later version.


Requirements

napwg requires to run:
- OpenRK 0.23.x.x or higher

to build and install:
- C compiler 
- make utility (eg, GNU make)
- OpenRk header

Installing 

Unpack the archive tarball change to the created directory and run the 
following commands:

    $ make
    $ make install (as root, or using sudo)


Running

To run napwg, simply type 'napwg' followed by the command line arguments,
type 'napwg -h' or 'napwg -help' to see the help

